[[include component:image-block | name=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Angus_Ridgway_Profile_Picture.jpg/640px-Angus_Ridgway_Profile_Picture.jpg | caption=SCP-XXXX instance. ]]

**Special Containment Procedures:** The public-facing business decisions of the consulting company, Taut Technologies Ltd., are to be monitored via web-scraping of news outlets and attendance to their quarterly general meetings. Notable business decisions include, but are not limited to, partnerships with other companies, investments to fund startups, and the construction of new Taut offices. 

The private business decisions of Taut are to be monitored by Foundation agents posing as Taut employees. Agents assigned at a Taut office must possess a CRV (Cognitive Resistance Value) of at least 31.00, and pass a psychological exam once a fortnight. Monitored Taut offices must be assigned no less than three (3) agents at a time [[footnote]]If one needs to take sick leave, others are encouraged to follow suit.[[/footnote]]. While working at such offices, agents should aim to stay within proximity of each other, and consistently remind each other of the Foundation's mission. Agents are to be reassigned elsewhere when they fail their psychological exam or four (4) months elapse, whichever occurs first. Offbosrded agents are to be administered Class C amnestics targeting their tenure in Taut.

The gathered information shall be used to launch smear campaigns to discredit Taut, bolster their business competitors, or otherwise inhibit Taut's socioeconomic influence, with the ultimate goal being its eventual dissolution. Via Protocol [REDACTED], the Foundation may force the liquidation of Taut as a last resort[[footnote]]Taut is entrenched in critical services supporting the welfare of several countries, and its abrupt disappearance would likely lead to a global recession.[[/footnote]].

Recruitment screenings of new Foundation personnel must include a thorough background check for any Taut work history. A retroactive screening of current personnel is underway.

**Description:** SCP-XXXX refers to a collection of humanoids employed by Taut Technologies [[footnote]]Foundation analysts estimate that SCP-XXXX comprises 22-25% of Taut's workforce.[[/footnote]], their partners and their subsidiaries. SCP-XXXX instances have resolute faith in Taut, and often expouse their company's ethos to their immediate colleagues. Prolonged exposure may cause affected colleagues to become new instances of SCP-XXXX. Empirical observation suggests that individuals higher up in the management hierarchy are more susceptible to SCP-XXXX.

The Taut ethos adapts to reflect the cultural values of its client organisations, and to a lesser extent, society at large. For example, the company slogan has changed from "World Wide Wealth" prior to the dot-com crash, to "Equality for all" at the height of the MeToo movement, to "Unblock your Blockhain" after the inception of Bitcoin, and to "All lives matter" following President Trump's inauguration. Regardless of evolving mores, a common sales pitch used by their consultants is to improve the working efficiency of their clients. Work inventories leaked by Foundation agents indicate mixed results.

Nevertheless, Taut seeks to expand the breadth of its international clientele. As typical of traded companies, Taut's primary goal is to maximise its market cap and appease its shareholders. 


[[include component:image-block | name=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Office_building%2C_on_Whiteladies_Road_-_geograph.org.uk_-_2281190.jpg/640px-Office_building%2C_on_Whiteladies_Road_-_geograph.org.uk_-_2281190.jpg | caption=Site 37's public-facing office. Subterranean complex not shown. ]]

**Discovery:** The Foundation made first contact with SCP-XXXX at Site-37, California. Site-37 doubles as the office of a front organisation, Solving Computer Problems, offering IT support services to the general population.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Dispatch Rendezvous CX-1134, two blocks south of Site-37**
@@@@
**13-09-2024T07:45:00 PST**

----

**Farleigh:** This is Bronze Eagle. Just landed at the perimeter.  
 
**[REDACTED]**: [REDACTED]

**Farleigh:** Mission parameters. Investigate Delta Charlie for conflicts of interest over [REDACTED].

**[REDACTED]**: [REDACTED]

**Farleigh:** Copy that. Code Yellow. And keep casualties at the minimum.

**[REDACTED]**: [REDACTED]

**Farleigh:** Affirmative, infiltrating under the pretense of a site transfer.

**[REDACTED]**: [REDACTED]

**Farleigh:** What about contingencies? For Code Reds, what's my backup?

**[REDACTED]**: [REDACTED] 

**Farleigh:** Understood. Eagle out.

[[/div]]


[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Reception, Site-37 Aboveground Premises**
@@@@
**13-09-2024T08:27:00 PST**

----

//A queue of civilians forms at Counter C1, manned by former agent Sophia Shraeder. The other counters are empty.//

**Tanvi:** So am I good to leave my baby here with you? I trust you'll take good care of it?

//Tanvi taps his desktop computer sitting on the reception.//

**Shraeder**: That's right. Our preliminary checks don't indicate anything too complicated. It should be done in two days.

**Tanvi:** Two days? Too easy.

**Shraeder:** Hey Max, could you please?

**SCP-XXXX-881:** Yeah no worries.

//SCP-XXXX-881 hefts Tanvi's computer and moves it back of house. Tanvi leaves and Horsman moves up the queue.//

**Horsman:** Hey, I'm...

**Shraeder:** Just a moment, please.

//Shraeder taps away at its keyboard. Clack clack clack.//

**Horsman:** ...

//Clack clack clack.//

**Horsman:** ...

//Clack clack clack.//

**Horsman:** How long is-

**Shraeder:** Hello, thanks for waiting. I'm Sophia, how may I help you?

**Horsman:** Hey, I'm here to pick up my keyboard. The name's Stu. Stu Horsman.

**Shraeder:** No problem. Let me look it up in the system.

**Horsman:** It's an Alienware. Model is Corsair K70 Pro.

**Shraeder:** Apologies Stu, it looks like your keyboard is still being worked on. Would you mind coming back next week?

//Horsman snickers and shakes his head.//

**Horsman:** Heh, that's what you told me last week. And the week before.

**Shraeder:** My sincere apologies Stu, we've been having a higher than average support volume. I'll let the technicians know and we'll move your product up in the priority-

**Horsman:** One of you already gave me the spiel last time. If this shit happens again-

//Horsman pauses and sighs.//

**Horsman:** Look, sorry, I've been here a couple times before, and you guys have been great. It's just that these past few weeks... I haven't had to wait for so long, you know?

**Shraeder:** Thank you for your feedback. It is appreciated. We'll take it under consideration.

//Horsman looks at Shraeder in the eye and sighs. After a moment, Horsman leaves and Farleigh moves up in the queue.//

**Farleigh:** ...

//Clack clack clack.//

**Farleigh:** ...

//Clack clack clack.//

**Farleigh:** Rough day, huh?

//Clack clack clack.//

**Shraeder:** Hello, thanks for waiting. I'm Sophia, how may I help you?

**Farleigh:** Hey Sophia, I'm here for the Bronze Eagle transmission unit.[[footnote]]Site-37 verbiage indicating a site transfer.[[/footnote]].

//Shraeder clacks away at its keyboard.//

**Shraeder:** Are you certain you dropped it off here? There's another repair store down the road which people sometimes mistake us for.

//Farleigh raises an eyebrow.//

**Farleigh:** Uh, yes, I'm sure.

**Shraeder:** May I have your name, or the date you left it with us?

**Farleigh:** ...no, that won't be necessary.

**Shraeder:** M-my apologies customer. I am not sure we're able to help you.

//Farleigh places her hand on the counter.//

**Farleigh:** //Ahem.// Bronze Eagle. Transmission unit. I'm sure you can find it in your system.

//Farleigh glances at the queue behind her, and leans closer to Shraeder.//

**Farleigh:** [[size smaller]]disable the civilian search filter, and look into database FF12.[[/size]]

//Shraeder tilts her head and twitches. She clacks away at her keyboard, and eventually invites Farleigh behind the counter.//

**Shraeder:** Ah- yes, of course. Your item has a few issues; do you mind coming to the back? Our technician will explain the details. Right this way, Marina Farleigh.

//Farleigh incredulously gazes at Shraeder, as she heads behind the reception. Simpson moves up the queue.//

**Simpson:** Hi, I've left my laptop here-

**Shraeder:** Just a moment, please.

//Clack clack clack.//

[[/div]]

